%% 07 Citation creation and source access | Detailed NodeJS/Core flow
sequenceDiagram
  participant RAG as Python RAG Service
  participant Node as NodeJS Core
  participant DB as MySQL
  participant Client as Web or Mobile Client
  participant Store as Local File Storage

  RAG-->>Node: Structured answer with source fragments and optional scores
  Node->>DB: Resolve vector_node_id to document_chunks and documents
  loop Each source fragment
    Node->>Node: Build immutable title, page, section, text and locator snapshot
    Note over Node: One parent chunk may produce multiple citation fragments
  end
  Node->>DB: Insert ordered citations in the assistant-completion transaction
  Note over Node,DB: Do not parse bracket markers such as [1], and retain snapshots after hide or delete

  Client->>Node: Request citation snapshot or original file with user JWT
  Node->>DB: Read citation, assistant message and chat session
  Node->>Node: Authorize chat-session owner or ADMIN
  alt Not authorized
    Node-->>Client: 404 citation not found
  else Snapshot requested
    Node-->>Client: Immutable source snapshot and originalAvailable
  else Original file requested
    Node->>DB: Read current document and source authorization context
    alt ADMIN or uploader and storage_key exists
      Node->>Store: Open file using internal storage_key
      Store-->>Node: File stream
      Node-->>Client: Stream file without exposing storage_key
    else Normal session owner and document is READY and VISIBLE
      Node->>Store: Open file using internal storage_key
      Store-->>Node: File stream
      Node-->>Client: Stream file without exposing storage_key
    else Original file is not authorized or unavailable by state
      Node-->>Client: 409 original source unavailable
    end
  end

  Note over Node,Store: If the database storage_key exists but the physical file is missing, the file endpoint returns 404 while the citation snapshot remains available
